      <h3>Listening Text – King Arthur: The Legend (Full Version)</h3>

      <h4>1. The Sword in the Stone</h4>
      <p>Long ago in medieval England, there lived a young boy named Arthur who worked as a servant for his older brother. One day, the kingdom held a great tournament because the old king died and England needed a new ruler. A mysterious sword appeared stuck in a large stone in the town square. The sword carried a magical inscription that said only the true king of England could pull it out. Many strong knights tried to remove the sword, but nobody succeeded. When Arthur touched the sword, it slid out easily from the stone. Everyone gasped in amazement and realized that Arthur was the rightful king of all England.</p>

      <h4>2. The Round Table and the Knights</h4>
      <p>After Arthur became king, he built a magnificent castle called Camelot in the heart of his kingdom. He created something very special - a huge Round Table where he invited the bravest and most honorable knights in the land to sit and discuss important matters. The table was perfectly round because Arthur believed that all his knights were equal and no one should sit at the head of the table. These knights promised to protect the weak, fight against evil, and always tell the truth. They traveled across dangerous forests and mountains to help people in trouble and complete difficult quests. The Knights of the Round Table became famous throughout the world for their courage and noble deeds.</p>

      <h4>3. Merlin the Wise Wizard</h4>
      <p>Merlin was an ancient and powerful wizard who became Arthur's closest friend and advisor. He wore long robes decorated with stars and moons, and he carried a wooden staff that glowed with magical energy. Merlin possessed extraordinary abilities - he could see visions of the future, transform into different animals, and cast powerful spells to protect the kingdom. When Arthur faced difficult decisions or dangerous enemies, he always consulted Merlin for wisdom and guidance. The old wizard taught Arthur important lessons about leadership, justice, and kindness. Without Merlin's magical help and wise counsel, Arthur's kingdom would have fallen to darkness many times.</p>

      <h4>4. The Quest for the Holy Grail</h4>
      <p>The most famous adventure of Arthur's knights was the quest to find the Holy Grail, a sacred cup that people believed had miraculous healing powers. According to the legend, only the purest and most virtuous knight could discover the Grail's secret location. Many knights departed from Camelot on this dangerous journey, riding through enchanted forests and battling fierce dragons. Sir Galahad, the youngest and noblest knight, eventually found the Holy Grail because his heart remained pure and he never gave up hope. The quest taught everyone an important lesson - true strength comes not from muscles or swords, but from courage, faith, and doing what is right even when the path seems impossible.</p>
